# Cursor Rules ‚Äî Citrus Care v1

> Cursor reads this automatically. Mirrors `CLAUDE.md` for cross-tool consistency.

## What this is
Photo-driven citrus tree care PWA. Snap a leaf, Gemini diagnoses, every tree keeps a timeline, re-assessment compares vs prior.

## Tech stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router) + React 19 + TS strict
- Tailwind 4 + shadcn/ui (`@base-ui/react` primitives)
- Supabase: Auth + Postgres (RLS) + Storage
- AI: `@google/genai` ‚Üí `gemini-2.5-flash` with `responseSchema`
- Cloudflare Turnstile on signup
- Vitest (unit) + Playwright (e2e)
- Vercel (Hobby tier)

## Commands
- `npm run dev` ‚Äî port 3002
- `npm run build` ‚Äî production build (script unsets NODE_ENV first; do not remove)
- `npm run lint` ‚Äî ESLint
- `npm test` ‚Äî Vitest
- `npx playwright test` ‚Äî e2e
- `npx tsc --noEmit` ‚Äî typecheck

## Key files
- `app/_lib/gemini.ts` ‚Äî vision + prompt + Zod
- `app/_lib/rate-limit.ts` ‚Äî Postgres rate limit
- `app/api/assess/route.ts` ‚Äî main AI endpoint
- `app/(auth)/*` ‚Äî auth + Turnstile
- `app/trees/*` ‚Äî tree CRUD + assess UI
- `proxy.ts` ‚Äî session + redirects
- `supabase/migrations/*.sql` ‚Äî schema + RLS

