## Hard rules (do not break)

- Gemini 2.5 Flash, `@google/genai`. No multi-provider fallback.
- All model JSON re-validated by Zod.
- RLS on every user-visible table. Service-role key never in user-facing routes.
- `photoPath.startsWith(user.id + "/")` before any Storage download.
- All error envelopes are generic strings; details `console.error` server-side.
- Rate limit `/api/assess`: 5/user/hour (`ASSESS_LIMIT_PER_HOUR`).
- Build script keeps `unset NODE_ENV`.
- Trunk-based. CI gates push.
- No new files unless necessary; edit existing first; refactor at 250 lines.
- No `tags:` field on any new Obsidian doc.

## Triage when no specific task

Modes A (new feature) / B (bug) / C (continue from latest) / D (summarize) / E (other). Ask which one. Don't assume.

## Session-end

Update Obsidian PRD ¬ß9, Security Log if relevant, Architecture ¬ßDecisions if a new one locked, `What I learned/` if non-obvious lesson.
